<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/dataproc/tools/</link><description>Recent content in Tools on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/dataproc/tools/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>dataproc-get-cluster</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/dataproc/tools/dataproc-get-cluster/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/dataproc/tools/dataproc-get-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;dataproc-get-cluster&lt;/code&gt; tool retrieves a specific Dataproc cluster from a
Google Cloud Dataproc source.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;dataproc-get-cluster&lt;/code&gt; accepts the following parameters:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;clusterName&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; The short name of the cluster to retrieve. e.g. for
&lt;code&gt;projects/my-project/regions/us-central1/clusters/my-cluster&lt;/code&gt;, pass
&lt;code&gt;my-cluster&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The tool gets the &lt;code&gt;project&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;region&lt;/code&gt; from the source configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="compatible-sources"&gt;Compatible Sources&lt;/h2&gt;





&lt;div class="compatibility-section"&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;This tool can be used with the following database sources:&lt;/p&gt;

